Jackie Chang

Bio

I am a research assistant in the Yu-Chao Wang Lab at National Yang Ming Chiao Tung University. In the lab, I am studying lung cancer through integrating multi-omics and machine learning approaches.

During my masters I studied host virus interaction, specifically through the post translational modification ADP-ribosylation, of SARS-CoV-2, Chikungunya, and Influenza with Anthony Leung at the Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health.

Education

Johns Hopkins University | Baltimore, MD

M.S. in Bioinformatics | December 2024

Vanderbilt University | Nashville, TN

B.A. in Biochemistry | May 2018

Research Experience

Bloomberg School of Public Health | Masters Student | Anthony Leung Lab | August 2023 - December 2024

Vanderbilt University Medical Center | Undergraduate Researcher | Bingshan Li Lab | June 2021 - May 2022

Academia Sinica | Undergraduate Researcher | Paul Verslues Lab | July 2020 - June 2021

Interests

  • Multi-Omics
  • Virus Host Interactions

Publications

R. Raja, B. Biswas, R. Abraham, H. Liu, C-Y. Chang, H. Vu, A.K.L. Leung. Interferon-Induced PARP14-Mediated ADP-Ribosylation in p62 Bodies Requires an Active Ubiquitin-Proteasome System. Embo J. https://doi.org/10.1038/s44318-025-00421-4
